# Intent Testing Patterns and Templates

## 🎯 Purpose

Test templates and patterns for intent integration testing. For debugging workflow, see `@intent-detection-debugging`. For specific issues, see `@intent-detection-issues`.

## 🧪 Integration Test Patterns

### Multi-Step Intent Flow Test

**Pattern**: Test complete user journey from initial request through parameter collection to completion.

```typescript
import { runMultiStepFlow } from "../chat/setup";

describe("[Intent Type] Integration", () => {
  it("should guide through [intent] with progressive suggestions", async () => {
    // Clean up before test
    await context.client.levva.cleanupChannel(
      context.channelId,
      context.userId
    );
    
    await runMultiStepFlow(context, [
      {
        // STEP 1: Initial request
        message: "I want to [action]",
        validate: (responses, suggestions) => {
          // Verify responses contain expected action
          const hasActionResponse = responses.some(
            (r) => r.rawMessage?.actions?.includes("[ACTION_NAME]")
          );
          expect(hasActionResponse).toBe(true);
          
          // Verify suggestions are relevant to first step
          const hasRelevantSuggestions = suggestions.some(
            (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("[keyword]")
          );
          expect(hasRelevantSuggestions).toBe(true);
          
          // Should NOT have completion suggestions yet
          const hasCompletionSuggestions = suggestions.some(
            (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("complete")
          );
          expect(hasCompletionSuggestions).toBe(false);
        },
      },
      {
        // STEP 2: Provide parameter
        message: "[specific parameter value]",
        validate: (responses, suggestions) => {
          // Verify progression to next step
          const hasNextStepSuggestions = suggestions.some(
            (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("[next keyword]")
          );
          expect(hasNextStepSuggestions).toBe(true);
          
          // Verify cancel option always available
          const hasCancelOption = suggestions.some(
            (s) => s.label.toLowerCase().includes("cancel")
          );
          expect(hasCancelOption).toBe(true);
        },
      },
    ]);
  });
});
```

**Real Example - Withdrawal Flow**:
```typescript
await runMultiStepFlow(context, [
  {
    // STEP 1: User requests withdrawal
    message: "I want to withdraw",
    validate: (responses, suggestions) => {
      // Verify withdrawal intent started
      const hasManagePositions = responses.some(
        (r) => r.rawMessage?.actions?.includes("MANAGE_POSITIONS")
      );
      expect(hasManagePositions).toBe(true);
      
      // Should show position-specific suggestions
      const hasPositionSuggestions = suggestions.filter(
        (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("withdraw") &&
              s.text.toLowerCase().includes("from")
      );
      expect(hasPositionSuggestions.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
    },
  },
  {
    // STEP 2: User selects position
    message: "Withdraw from Safe yield",
    validate: (responses, suggestions) => {
      // Should show amount suggestions
      const hasAmountSuggestions = suggestions.filter(
        (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("withdraw") &&
              /\d+/.test(s.text) // Has numbers
      );
      expect(hasAmountSuggestions.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
      
      // Should NOT have "specify custom amount" (users can type directly)
      const hasCustomAmountSuggestion = suggestions.some(
        (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("custom amount")
      );
      expect(hasCustomAmountSuggestion).toBe(false);
    },
  },
]);
```

### Informational vs Action Test

**Pattern**: Verify informational requests don't trigger transaction intents.

```typescript
it("should NOT trigger [ACTION] intent for informational requests", async () => {
  // Clean up before test
  await context.client.levva.cleanupChannel(channelId, userId);
  await context.client.messaging.clearChannelHistory(channelId);
  
  // Send informational request
  const responses = await sendMessageAndWaitForComplete(
    context,
    "Analyze my [domain-specific-thing]"
  );
  
  // Wait for suggestions
  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 3000));
  
  const suggestionsResponse = await context.client.levva.getSuggestions(
    userAddress,
    channelId,
    chainId
  );
  
  const suggestions = suggestionsResponse.suggestions;
  
  // CRITICAL: Should NOT have action-specific suggestions
  const hasActionSuggestions = suggestions.some(
    (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("[action-keyword]")
  );
  expect(hasActionSuggestions).toBe(false);
  
  // Should have informational suggestions instead
  const hasInfoSuggestions = suggestions.some(
    (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("position") ||
          s.text.toLowerCase().includes("strategy") ||
          s.text.toLowerCase().includes("portfolio")
  );
  expect(hasInfoSuggestions).toBe(true);
  
  // Verify no intent was created
  console.log("\n🔍 Suggestions for informational request:");
  suggestions.forEach((s, i) => {
    console.log(`  ${i + 1}. "${s.label}" - ${s.text}`);
  });
});
```

**Real Example - Portfolio Analysis**:
```typescript
it("should NOT trigger SEND intent for general portfolio analysis", async () => {
  await context.client.levva.cleanupChannel(channelId, userId);
  await context.client.messaging.clearChannelHistory(channelId);
  
  const responses = await sendMessageAndWaitForComplete(
    context,
    "Analyze my portfolio"
  );
  
  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 3000));
  
  const suggestionsResponse = await context.client.levva.getSuggestions(
    ADDRESS,
    channelId,
    TEST_CONFIG.chainId
  );
  
  const suggestions = suggestionsResponse.suggestions;
  
  // Should NOT have SEND suggestions
  const hasSendSuggestions = suggestions.some(
    (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("send") ||
          s.text.toLowerCase().includes("transfer")
  );
  expect(hasSendSuggestions).toBe(false);
  
  // Should have portfolio-related suggestions
  const hasPortfolioSuggestions = suggestions.some(
    (s) => s.text.toLowerCase().includes("position") ||
          s.text.toLowerCase().includes("strategy")
  );
  expect(hasPortfolioSuggestions).toBe(true);
});
```

### Test Setup and Teardown

```typescript
import { setupChatTest, teardownChatTest, ChatTestContext } from "./setup";

describe("[Intent Type] Suggestions Integration", () => {
  let context: ChatTestContext;
  
  beforeEach(async () => {
    context = await setupChatTest();
    
    // Additional setup if needed
    await context.client.levva.cleanupChannel(
      context.channelId,
      context.userId
    );
  });
  
  afterEach(async () => {
    await teardownChatTest(context);
  });
  
  // Tests...
});
```

## 📋 Test Helper Functions

### runMultiStepFlow

**Purpose**: Execute multi-step conversations and validate each step.

**Location**: `__tests__/chat/setup.ts`

**Usage**:
```typescript
await runMultiStepFlow(context, [
  {
    message: "User message",
    validate: async (responses, suggestions) => {
      // Validation logic
      expect(responses.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
      expect(suggestions.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
    },
  },
  // More steps...
]);
```

**Features**:
- Automatically waits for agent responses
- Fetches suggestions after each step
- Provides both responses and suggestions to validator
- Cleans up between steps if needed

### sendMessageAndWaitForComplete

**Purpose**: Send a message and wait for all agent responses.

**Location**: `__tests__/chat/setup.ts`

**Usage**:
```typescript
const responses = await sendMessageAndWaitForComplete(
  context,
  "User message text"
);

console.log(`Received ${responses.length} responses`);
responses.forEach((r, i) => {
  console.log(`${i + 1}. Action: ${r.rawMessage?.actions?.[0] || "NONE"}`);
  console.log(`   Text: ${r.text?.substring(0, 100)}...`);
});
```

**Returns**: Array of agent responses with metadata.

## ✅ Checklist for New Intent Tests

### Test File Structure
- [ ] Import required helpers from `../chat/setup`
- [ ] Use `describe` block for intent type
- [ ] Set up `beforeEach` with cleanup
- [ ] Set up `afterEach` with teardown

### Test Coverage
- [ ] **Multi-step flow test**: Complete user journey
- [ ] **Informational request test**: Verify intent doesn't trigger
- [ ] **Parameter validation**: Each step has correct suggestions
- [ ] **Cancel flow**: User can cancel at any step
- [ ] **Edge cases**: Empty data, invalid params, etc.

### Validation Checks
- [ ] Verify correct action in responses (`MANAGE_POSITIONS`, `SWAP_TOKENS`, etc.)
- [ ] Check suggestion relevance to current step
- [ ] Ensure progressive disclosure (don't show all params at once)
- [ ] Validate suggestion format (user-facing text, not agent-facing)
- [ ] Confirm cancel option always available
- [ ] Check no "custom amount/value" suggestions (users can type)

### Cleanup and State
- [ ] Call `cleanupChannel` before each test
- [ ] Use `TEST_CONFIG.chainId` instead of hardcoded values
- [ ] Verify no stale intents after cleanup
- [ ] Test timeout set appropriately (30s+ for integration tests)

## 📝 Key Files Reference

### Test Files
- `__tests__/chat/setup.ts` - Test helpers and configuration
  - `setupChatTest()` - Initialize test context
  - `teardownChatTest()` - Cleanup after test
  - `runMultiStepFlow()` - Multi-step conversation helper
  - `sendMessageAndWaitForComplete()` - Send message and wait
  - `TEST_CONFIG` - Test configuration (chainId, address, etc.)

- `__tests__/suggestions/*.integration.test.ts` - Intent flow tests
  - `withdrawal.integration.test.ts` - WITHDRAW intent tests
  - `deposit.integration.test.ts` - DEPOSIT intent tests
  - `swap.integration.test.ts` - SWAP intent tests
  - `send.integration.test.ts` - SEND intent tests

### Source Files (Test Targets)
- `src/services/intent-manager.ts` - Intent lifecycle management
- `src/prompts/intent.ts` - Intent detection prompt
- `src/evaluators/suggestions.ts` - Suggestion generation
- `src/routes/cleanup.ts` - Channel cleanup endpoint
- `src/actions/intents/*.ts` - Intent handlers

### Configuration
- `__tests__/chat/setup.ts::TEST_CONFIG` - Test environment config
  ```typescript
  export const TEST_CONFIG = {
    baseUrl: process.env.ELIZA_BASE_URL || "http://localhost:3001",
    secret: SECRET,
    address: ADDRESS as `0x${string}`,
    chainId: 1, // Always use constant, never hardcode
    timeout: 30000,
  } as const;
  ```

## 🎯 Test Quality Guidelines

### Good Test Characteristics
- ✅ **Isolated**: Each test cleans up before/after
- ✅ **Deterministic**: Same input always produces same result
- ✅ **Fast**: Use appropriate timeouts, don't wait unnecessarily
- ✅ **Readable**: Clear test names and validation messages
- ✅ **Maintainable**: Use helpers, avoid duplication

### Bad Test Patterns
- ❌ **Flaky**: Depends on timing or external state
- ❌ **Brittle**: Breaks when unrelated code changes
- ❌ **Slow**: Unnecessary waits or delays
- ❌ **Vague**: Unclear what's being tested
- ❌ **Duplicated**: Copy-pasted code instead of helpers

### Debugging Failed Tests

```bash
# 1. Check test output for specific failure
bun test __tests__/suggestions/[intent].integration.test.ts -t "test name"

# 2. Check server logs
grep "INTENT-DETECTION\|SUGGESTIONS\|CLEANUP" dev.log | tail -100

# 3. Verify cleanup worked
grep "CLEANUP.*cleanup complete" dev.log | tail -5

# 4. Check for stale intents
grep "FALLBACK domain" dev.log | tail -10

# 5. Verify correct chainId
grep "chainId" dev.log | grep -v "8453\|42161" | tail -20
```

